[0m[49m[39m  174, 157[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  175, 158[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  176, 159[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  177, 160[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 178     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | AWS Services | SageMaker, Lambda, DynamoDB, S3, Step Functions, EventBridge, QuickSight, API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 179     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | IAM Permissions | sagemaker:CreateProcessingJob, lambda:InvokeFunction, dynamodb:PutItem/GetItem/Query, s3:GetObject/PutObject, states:StartExecution |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 180     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | BAA | Required. Block schedules contain surgeon names and may reference patient case types. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 181     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Encryption | S3 SSE-KMS, DynamoDB encryption at rest, TLS in transit |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 182     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | VPC | Recommended for SageMaker jobs accessing on-premises EHR data |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 183     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | CloudTrail | Audit logging for all optimization runs and allocation changes |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 184     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Sample Data | Synthetic OR case data with realistic duration distributions. Never use real patient data in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 185     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | Cost Estimate | ~$200-400/month for daily release management (Lambda + DynamoDB). ~$400-800/month including quarterly SageMaker optimization runs. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Lambda, S3, ECS (Fargate), DynamoDB, EventBridge, SageMaker, QuickSight |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `ecs:RunTask`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `events:PutRule` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | Required if scheduling data includes patient identifiers (it typically does: surgeon names, case types by patient) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; ECS: encrypt task storage; all transit over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Fargate tasks and Lambda in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all optimization runs and schedule modifications for audit trail |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Solver License** | If using Gurobi/CPLEX: cloud license (token server or machine ID based). If using open-source (HiGHS, CBC): no license needed. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic OR utilization data. Use realistic distributions: 60-85% utilization, 5-15% cancellation rate, 10-50 rooms. Never use actual patient/surgeon identifiers in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | SageMaker inference: ~$5-20/month for weekly forecasts. Fargate solver tasks: ~$0.50-5 per solve (depends on problem size and duration). Lambda, DynamoDB, S3: negligible. Total: $50-200/month for weekly batch optimization. |
[0m[49m[39m  186, 170[0m:[39m[49m 
